entries.meaning: Before a molar tooth, either in physical position or in its time of development; deciduous.
A tooth situated in front of the molar teeth; especially a tooth in humans with two cusps which is between the canines and the molars (Latin: singular dens premolaris, plural dentes premolares)
examples: He opened and let out a hogo of medicinal rum and beer. The bad tooth was a premolar.
